  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It is a collection of 50 papers from NIPS 2008-2013, 50 from ICML 2009-2014, and 50 from AAAI 2009-2014, selecting 10 published papers at random from each conference and year.",
    "Images, tables, and captions have been labeled by experts using the LabelMe tool [33].",
    "In 2016, the authors released a larger version of the dataset called CS-Large [61] by randomly sampling 346 papers from Semantic Scholar [68] published after 1999.",
    "The authors also propose PDFFigures 2.0 [61], a tool built on top of the previous version for a wider range of different styles and layouts (tested on CS-Large).",
    "It is based on datadriven heuristics, which exploit formatting conventions used consistently in the computer science domain."
  ],
